Package kaitech.api.database

Interface RecipeTable

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    RecipeTblImpl
    public interface RecipeTable
    The RecipeTable interface declares required functionality to store, retrieve, and modify recipes in the database.

    • Method Summary

    • Method Detail

      • getRecipe

        Recipe getRecipe​(int id)
        Retrieves a recipe from the cache. If the recipe does not currently exist in the cache, query the database for the recipe. If the query is successful, add the recipe to the cache and return it.
        Parameters:
        id - The integer ID of the recipe to be retrieved.
        Returns:
        A Recipe if the recipe exists, null if it does not.

      • getAllIDNo

        java.util.Set<java.lang.Integer> getAllIDNo()
        Get all IDs for recipes currently in the database.
        Returns:
        A set of all integer recipe IDs.

      • putRecipe

        Recipe putRecipe​(Recipe from)
        Saves a given recipe to the database, and returns a database managed Recipe which is responsible for the automatic saving of changes on setter calls.
        Parameters:
        from - The Recipe to be saved.
        Returns:
        Database managed Recipe responsible for automatic saving on setter calls.

      • removeRecipe

        void removeRecipe​(int id)
        Remove a recipe from the database and cache.
        Parameters:
        id - The ID number of the recipe to be removed.

      • resolveAllRecipes

        java.util.Map<java.lang.Integer,​Recipe> resolveAllRecipes()
        Gets all recipe objects from the database. Warning: this can be a costly operation when everything isn't already cached, please use with care.
        Returns:
        A map from recipe ID to Recipe.

      • getOrAddRecipe

        default Recipe getOrAddRecipe​(Recipe from)
        From a given Recipe, gets or creates the database equivalent.
        Parameters:
        from - The Recipe to have its database equivalent retrieved or added.
        Returns:
        Database managed Recipe responsible for automatic saving on setter calls.
